{"id": "69c18970-017d-4fc9-ae2e-71bf12ae466a", "url": "http://ipt.iobis.org/obiscanada/resource?r=biochem_bb1967_frb_r120", "archive": "https://ipt.iobis.org/obiscanada/archive.do?r=biochem_bb1967_frb_r120", "published": "2026-02-11T17:54:54.000Z", "created": null, "updated": "2026-02-11T18:01:32.937Z", "core": "occurrence", "extensions": [], "statistics": {"Event": 0, "absence": 99, "dropped": 0, "Occurrence": 464, "DNADerivedData": 0, "MeasurementOrFact": 0}, "extent": "POLYGON((-63.635 44.6833,-63.635 44.6833,-63.635 44.6833,-63.635 44.6833,-63.635 44.6833))", "title": "BioChem: Diatom and dinoflagellate profiles collected in Bedford Basin, January to October 1967", "citation": "DFO (2013).  Diatom and dinoflagellate profiles collected in Bedford Basin, January to October 1967. Version 1 In OBIS Canada Digital Collections. Bedford Institute of Oceanography, Dartmouth, NS, Canada. Published by OBIS, Digital http://www.iobis.org/. Accessed on \u2013INSERT DATE", "citation_id": "http://iobis.org/mapper/?resource_id=2802", "abstract": "\n            <p>This resource contains species distribution records extracted from the Fisheries and Oceans Canada BioChem database for the BioChem 'BedfordBasin1967_FRB_R120' series of records.  This collection contains diatom and dinoflagellate abundance and depth distribution information obtained as part of a 1967 sampling program in the Bedford Basin.  \n\nSamples were collected using water bottles at 7 discrete depths from the surface to 60m. Lugol preserved samples were analysed and the counts per litre of diatoms and dinoflagellates were recorded.\n\nSample analysis results were archived in the BioChem database.  This OBIS resource contains a subset of these database records - at this time only abundance information has been released. These data appear to be archived in BioChem with the mission name BEDBAS67.</p>\n        ", "intellectualrights": "This work is licensed under a  Creative Commons Attribution (CC-BY 4.0) License",